ext-align:left}li{color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:"Calibri"}p{margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:"Calibri"}h1{padding-top:24pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:24pt;padding-bottom:6pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h2{padding-top:18pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:18pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h3{padding-top:14pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:14pt;padding-bottom:4pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h4{padding-top:12pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:12pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h5{padding-top:11pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:11pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}h6{padding-top:10pt;color:#000000;font-weight:700;font-size:10pt;padding-bottom:2pt;font-family:"Calibri";line-height:1.0;page-break-after:avoid;orphans:2;widows:2;text-align:left}</style></head><body class="c11 doc-content"><p class="c5"><span class="c8">Waiver:</span></p><p class="c5 c10"><span class="c9"></span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">2022 NWSL Championship Fan Fest &ndash; Speed Kick Challenge<br>ACKNOWLEDGEMENT AND RELEASE (the &ldquo;Release&rdquo;)</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c1">For good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged, you, the undersigned (&ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Releasor</span><span class="c1">,&rdquo; provided that if Releasor is a minor under the applicable age of majority (18 years of age in most states), &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Releasor</span><span class="c1">&rdquo; shall include such minor and his/her parent or legal guardian, both on behalf of such minor and such parent or guardian) hereby voluntarily agrees as follows in connection with all of the events and activities held in connection with the 2022 NWSL Championship, including, but not limited to, the 2022 NWSL Fan Fest and other related events (including the Speed Kick Challenge) to be held in and around Washington, D.C., including, but not limited to, Audi Field (with each of its surrounding parking lots, concourses, staging, and such other areas immediately adjacent thereto) from on or about October 29, 2022 (collectively, the &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Championship Events</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;), in which Releasor attends or otherwise participates:</span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">1.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">RELEASE FROM LIABILITY AND COVENANT NOT TO INSTITUTE LEGAL PROCEEDINGS</span><span class="c3">.&nbsp; </span><span class="c1">Releasor hereby irrevocably undertakes and agrees, for himself/herself and his/her personal representatives, executors, liquidators, administrators, heirs, next of kin, successors, agents and assigns, and anyone else who might sue on Releasor&rsquo;s behalf (collectively with the Releasor, the &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Releasor Parties</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;), to release, waive, indemnify, hold harmless and discharge National Women&rsquo;s Soccer League, LLC (&ldquo;</span><span class="c3">NWSL</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;), each member club of the NWSL and each owner of a member club of the NWSL, DC United Soccer Club, DC Stadium, LLC, each owner and operator of any Championship Event, arena or venue in which Championship Events are held, each sponsor (including CarMax Enterprise Services, LLC, and its related parties and affiliates and subsidiaries), promoter and advertiser of any Championship Event or any part of them, each person or entity engaged by NWSL as an independent contractor or otherwise in connection with any Championship Event, any NWSL member club or any venue operator, the National Women&rsquo;s Soccer League Players&rsquo; Association and each former and current NWSL player, and each of their respective parents, subsidiaries, stockholders, partners and other affiliates and related persons or entities, and each officer, director, governor, regent, trustee, employee, volunteer, licensor, licensee, insurer, sponsor, partner, principal, representative and agent of each of the foregoing, and all of the foregoing&rsquo;s respective successors and assigns (collectively, &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Releasees</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;), from and against any and all liabilities, losses (economic and non-economic), damages, liens, actions, obligations, judgments, orders, costs, expenses (including, but not limited to, attorneys&rsquo; fees and expenses), causes of action, suits and claims of any nature whatsoever (collectively, the &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Liabilities</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;) which any Releasor Party had, now has, or hereafter may have, including any Liabilities which any minor Releasor or Releasor Party has or hereafter may acquire, either before or after he/she has reached his or her majority, by reason of any matter directly or indirectly arising out of or connected in any way with the Championship Events, including, without limitation, those arising from, whether directly or indirectly, based upon or relating to bodily injury or death to, or damage to or loss of property of Releasor, sustained in connection with Releasor&rsquo;s participation in any event, clinic, competition, demonstration, exhibition, practice, game or activity associated with or comprising the Championship Events, including, but not limited to, any soccer activity at the 2022 NWSL FanFest, including the Skills Competition, the 2022 Championship Game, any sponsor event, any media event, any member club event, or travel to or from any Championship Event and the grant of rights hereunder (including arising out of or in connection with the Materials, as defined below). Such release, waiver, indemnification, hold harmless and discharge shall include, but not be limited to, any and all such Liabilities caused in whole or in part by the fault or negligence of any Releasee in connection with such Releasee&rsquo;s involvement with any Championship Event. Without limiting the foregoing, Releasor, on behalf of all Releasor Parties, covenants and agrees to waive any claim and not to institute legal proceedings against any Releasees for any of the Liabilities that have been released and discharged herein.&nbsp; </span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">2.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">RELEASOR ASSUMES RISK</span><span class="c3">.&nbsp; </span><span class="c1">Releasor hereby acknowledges and declares that he/she has been made aware of and understands the inherent risks (both known and unknown) and dangers (direct or indirect) associated with the Championship Events, including those related to the sport of soccer, and the potential for injury and/or damages that exists when participating in such Championship Events.&nbsp; Releasor hereby agrees to assume all risk of and responsibility for personal injury or death to, or damage to or loss of property of Releasor arising from, based upon or relating to Releasor&rsquo;s participation in connection with any Championship Event or caused, in whole or in part, by Releasor&rsquo;s fault or negligence. Such assumption of risk includes, but is not limited to any damage to or loss of property, arising from, based upon or relating to the lack of skill of any participant in any Championship Event, or caused in whole or in part by the negligence of any Releasee. Releasor hereby understands and has been made aware that, in the event of any injury to Releasor, none of Releasees will be responsible for any decisions relating to medical care, decisions or treatment for Releasor or for such treatment itself including, without limitations, any costs and/or expenses incurred in connection therewith.</span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">3.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">REPRESENTATIONS</span><span class="c3">.&nbsp; </span><span class="c1">Releasor acknowledges that Releasor&rsquo;s participation in any Championship Events is conditioned on Releasor&rsquo;s consent to the terms of this Release. Releasor hereby represents and warrants that he/she has had full opportunity to ask any questions regarding Championship Events that he/she may have and that he/she has read understood and declared, himself/herself satisfied with the contents of this Release (and, if applicable, that his/her parent or legal guardian has read, understood and declared themselves satisfied with this Release, and has sufficiently explained it to Releasor) and that he/she has been given an opportunity to review this Release with anyone he/she chooses, including a lawyer, and has done so to the extent he/she wishes to do so. Releasor further represents and warrants that Releasor is in good physical condition, is physically fit to participate in the Championship Events and is not subject to any medical condition that poses or may pose any risk of harm or disability to Releasor or to others.&nbsp; Releasor further represents and warrants that he/she is of sound mind and body and not under the influence of alcohol or any other drug or medication which may in any way impair Releasor&rsquo;s ability to enter into this Release, fully understand the intent and meaning of all the terms and provisions of this Release, or participate safely in the Championship Events.&nbsp; Releasor acknowledges and agrees that his/her participation in the Championship Events is voluntary and solely for his/her benefit and entertainment.&nbsp; Releasor understands that he/she can withdraw from the Championship Events at any time. Releasor acknowledges and agrees that he/she will not be compensated by any of the Releasees for participating in any of the Championship Events. </span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">4.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">RIGHT OF PUBLICITY</span><span class="c3">.&nbsp; </span><span class="c1">Releasor hereby grants to Releasees and any of their designees the unrestricted, royalty-free, irrevocable, perpetual, non-exclusive, fully paid-up right and license to (a) take photographs, make audiovisual recordings, and otherwise use the name, image and/or likeness of Releasor in connection with his/her participation at or in any of the Championship Events (the &ldquo;</span><span class="c3">Materials</span><span class="c1">&rdquo;) and (b) reproduce, copy, publish, display, distribute, perform, translate, adapt, publicly present, communicate to the public by telecommunications, copyright, exhibit, license, modify, edit, create digitized images of, juxtapose, synchronize, broadcast, reuse, create derivative works from and otherwise exploit or use and permit to be used such Materials or any part thereof, whether alone or in combination with other materials, in each case without notice or right of prior review or approval, in any and all markets in any and all media now known or hereafter devised in perpetuity throughout the universe. In connection with the foregoing, Releasor hereby consents and authorizes Releasees to use, and authorize the use of, the name, image/likeness, photograph (still and moving), picture, voice recording, performance, and/or any other identification of Releasor for any and all purposes, including, without limitation, advertising, publicity, instructional, sales relating thereto or any other purposes in connection with the Championship Events or Releasees and their goods, services or other businesses, in any and all media now known or hereafter devised in perpetuity throughout the universe, without compensation, notice or right of prior review or approval (to the extent permitted by law). Releasor agrees, for all Releasor Parties, to release and discharge each Releasee from, to waive in respect of each Releasee, and not to institute legal proceedings against any Releasee for, any and all Liabilities arising from, based upon or relating to any claim for invasion of privacy, violation of right of publicity, defamation or appropriation, or any similar claim any Releasor Parties may have now or in the future, whether known or unknown, in connection with any such use.&nbsp; Releasor, on behalf of all Releasor Parties, hereby waives and releases any and all claims that he/she may have or hereafter have against the Releasees under any other statutes or common law principles of similar effect.&nbsp; </span></p><p class="c0"><span class="c3">5.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">NO OBLIGATION OF RELEASEES</span><span class="c3">. </span><span class="c1">&nbsp;None of Releasees shall have, or be deemed to have, any obligation to Releasor or any other Releasor Parties hereunder or otherwise in connection with any Championship Event unless set forth in writing signed by Releasor and Releasee.&nbsp; Releasor understands that the Releasees do not carry or maintain health, medical or disability insurance coverage for Releasor. Each Releasor is expected and encouraged to obtain his or her own medical or health insurance coverage.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c3">6.&nbsp; </span><span class="c4">MISCELLANEOUS</span><span class="c3">.&nbsp; </span><span class="c1">This Release shall constitute the entire understanding between Releasor and the Releasees with respect to the subjects discussed in this Release.&nbsp; This Release shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York, without giving effect to its conflicts of law principles.&nbsp; If any portion of the Release shall be held invalid or unenforceable, the remaining portion hereof shall not be affected thereby and shall remain in full force and effect. Releasor expressly consents that this Release shall be given full force and effect according to each and all of its express terms and provisions, including, without limitation, those related to unknown and unsuspected claims.&nbsp; </span></p><p class="c5"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">I HAVE READ THIS RELEASE AND FULLY UNDERSTAND ITS TERMS AND THEIR SIGNIFICANCE.&nbsp; </span><span class="c3">I AM AWARE THAT THIS RELEASE INCLUDES A RELEASE AND WAIVER OF LIABILITY, AN ASSUMPTION OF RISK AND AN AGREEMENT TO INDEMNIFY THE RELEASEES.&nbsp; I UNDERSTAND I HAVE GIVEN UP RIGHTS THAT MAY OTHERWISE BE AVAILABLE BY SIGNING (BY CHECKING THE BOX BELOW) THIS RELEASE.</span><span class="c1">&nbsp;I HAVE SIGNED THIS RELEASE BY CHECKING THE BOX BELOW FREELY AND VOLUNTARILY WITHOUT ANY COERCION, INDUCEMENT, ASSURANCE OR GUARANTEE.</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">&nbsp;</span></p><hr style="page-break-before:always;display:none;"><p class="c7"><span class="c3">[&nbsp; ] By checking this box, you acknowledge that you have read and understand the Release terms above, including the limitation of liability, and you hereby understand and agree that you will be bound by such Release.</span></p><p class="c7"><span class="c3">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="c2"><span class="c1">[ </span><span class="c3">] By checking this box, if you are a parent (or legal guardian or the person having parental authority) of a minor who has signed in to participate, you hereby agree, on behalf of said minor and on your own behalf, that you and the said minor will be bound by all the provisions contained herein.&nbsp; You represent and warrant that you have legal custody of said minor, that you have the authority to enter into this Release on behalf of said minor and on your own behalf and that you have read this Release and fully understand its terms and their significance as applied to said minor and to yourself.&nbsp; You hereby agree to indemnify and hold the Releasees harmless from and against any Liabilities arising out of a breach of the foregoing representation and warranty.</span></p><p class="c5 c10"><span class="c6"></span></p></body></html>